    <h1>Forward Reserve Wye-Delta Motor Control Diagram</h1>

    <p>The Wye-Delta motor starting method is used to reduce the starting current of the motor. This method is often used in applications where the motor has to start under a light load and the reduction in current draw is crucial. The forward reserve Wye-Delta method involves initially connecting the motor in a Wye (Star) configuration and then switching to a Delta configuration.</p>

    <h2>Components Involved</h2>
    <ul>
        <li>Three-Phase Motor</li>
        <li>Wye-Delta Starter</li>
        <li>Control Circuit</li>
        <li>Power Circuit</li>
        <li>Timers</li>
        <li>Contactors</li>
        <li>Overload Relays</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Control Circuit Diagram</h2>
    <div class="diagram">
        <img src="https://via.placeholder.com/800x400" alt="Control Circuit Diagram">
    </div>

    <h2>Power Circuit Diagram</h2>
    <div class="diagram">
        <img src="https://via.placeholder.com/800x400" alt="Power Circuit Diagram">
    </div>

    <h2>Explanation of Operation</h2>
    <p>The Wye-Delta starter works in two stages:</p>
    <ol>
        <li><strong>Wye (Star) Starting:</strong> Initially, the motor is connected in a Wye configuration, which reduces the voltage across each winding to 1/âˆš3 (approximately 58%) of the line voltage. This significantly reduces the starting current and torque.</li>
        <li><strong>Delta Running:</strong> After a preset time delay (usually controlled by a timer), the motor is switched to a Delta configuration. In this configuration, the motor receives the full line voltage, allowing it to run at full speed and torque.</li>
    </ol>

    <h2>Interactive Elements</h2>
    <div class="interactive">
        <label for="timer">Set Timer for Wye to Delta Transition (seconds):</label>
        <input type="number" id="timer" name="timer" min="1" max="60" value="10">
        <button onclick="setTimer()">Set Timer</button>
        <p id="timer-display"></p>
    </div>

    <script>
        function setTimer() {
            const timerValue = document.getElementById('timer').value;
            document.getElementById('timer-display').innerText = `Timer set to ${timerValue} seconds`;
        }
    </script>

